# Portfolio Project Guidelines

## Project Structure

### URL Paths
- Professional projects: `/work/<project-id>`
- Personal/hobby projects: `/lab/<project-id>`

## Content Guidelines

### Project Descriptions
- Keep descriptions professional but concise (2-3 sentences)
- Always start with "I built/developed/created/designed" to clearly establish ownership
- Include who the project was for (client or target audience)
- Highlight key metrics and impact where applicable
- Mention key technologies only when relevant
- Avoid unnecessary adjectives and wordiness

### Project Subtitles
- Professional projects: "for [Company Name]"
- Personal projects: "Personal Project" or specific category

## Featured Work Format

```typescript
{
  id: "project-id",
  title: "Project Title",
  subtitle: "for Company / Personal Project",
  description: [
    "I developed/built/created [what] for [whom]. This [solution/project] [key impact/metrics].",
  ],
  imageSrc: projectCoverImage,
  imageAlt: "Descriptive alt text for the project image",
  link: {
    url: "/work/project-id" or "/lab/project-id",
    text: "View Project",
  },
}
```

## UI Components

### Text Highlighting
- Use the `<TextHighlight>` component for emphasizing key phrases
- Apply sparingly to maintain visual hierarchy
- Focus on highlighting metrics, technical innovations, and key benefits

### Code Components
- `CodeBlock`: For multi-line code examples with syntax highlighting
- `InlineCode`: For short code snippets within text

## Case Study Structure
1. Overview/Introduction
2. Challenge/Problem
3. Solution
4. Technical Implementation
5. Results/Impact
6. Key Takeaways

## Image Guidelines
- Use high-quality screenshots
- Include descriptive alt text
- Maintain consistent aspect ratios when possible 